mqtt-grafana
============

Read-only SQLite-to-JSON CGI endpoint for the Freetz web server on port 81.

Installed URL:
  http://fritz.box:81/cgi-bin/mqtt-grafana.cgi

Power dashboard:
  http://fritz.box:81/mqtt-grafana.html

The dashboard obtains its power topic from the endpoint's runtime configuration
and displays its current value and history over the last 48 hours. It refreshes
every five seconds. The page and endpoint are served from the same authenticated
Freetz web server, so the browser reuses the port-81 authentication and no
credentials are handled by JavaScript.

Parameters:
  from=UNIX_SECONDS       default: now - 3600
  to=UNIX_SECONDS         default: now
  topic=MQTT_TOPIC        optional exact match
  limit=ROWS              default: 2000, capped by runtime value
  mode=health             database health/latest timestamp response
  mode=config             dashboard topic and maximum-row response

Example:
  /cgi-bin/mqtt-grafana.cgi?topic=sensor/temp&from=1700000000&to=1700003600

The endpoint returns timestamps in milliseconds for Grafana and preserves the
original payload. A numeric value field is set when the complete payload is a
valid finite number.

Build notes:
The CGI links libm after libsqlite3 because numeric MQTT payload handling uses
floating-point classification functions such as isfinite(). SQLite headers
come from the target staging directory populated by the declared sqlite
dependency. When the esp32c3 integration is installed, the database path,
exact dashboard topic, maximum rows, and allowed client address are read from
the persistent /mod/etc/conf/esp32c3.cfg on every request. The dashboard topic
is deliberately separate from mqtt2sqlite's wildcard subscriptions.
